Scientific name: Anas platyrhynchos

The mallard is the commonest and most widespread duck in the UK. The breeding male has a distinctive
glossy bottle-green head, a white collar separating its head from its purple tinged brown breast, grey-
brown wings, a pale grey belly and its bill is yellowish-orange tipped with black. The female is altogether less
colourful being generally much more mottled with buff to darker coloured feathers.

Mallards breed in all parts of the UK, wherever there are suitable wetland habitats. The female
will lay between 8 and 13 creamy white to greenish-buff eggs with no speckles. Incubation
takes 27 to 28 days and fledging takes between 50 to 60 days. As soon as the ducklings

hatch, they are able to swim. @sBAcus

Scientific name: Anas platyrhynchos

The mallard is the commonest and most widespread duck in the UK. The breeding male has a distinctive
glossy bottle-green head, a white collar separating its head from its purple tinged brown breast, grey-
brown wings, a pale grey belly and its bill is yellowish-orange tipped with black. The female is altogether less
colourful being generally much more mottled with buff to darker coloured feathers.

Mallards breed in all parts of the UK, wherever there are suitable wetland habitats. The female
will lay between 8 and 13 creamy white to greenish-buff eggs with no speckles. Incubation
takes 27 to 28 days and fledging takes between 50 to 60 days. As soon as the ducklings

hatch, they are able to swim. @sBAcus

What is BODAQ HOME?
Bodaq Homes a self-adhesive decorative vinyl for interiors. It is a versatile material for diverse
applications, easy and clean to install. Easily cut by hand or with the aid of a cameo cutter, vinyl cutter
or any similar device.
Includes a printed grid backing pattern on its back that facilitates precise cuts.

The surface to be applied on must be free of grease and dust, it must be completely smooth, such as
flattened walls, drywall, plastic or metal sheets, MDF boards, melamine and others.

tis recommended to cut exceedingly by approximately 1.1 to 1.9 in.

Installation:
Make sure that the surface is smooth, free of dust and grease, without textures or imperfections.
Peel off 1.1 to 1.9 in of the backing paper and fix.

Maintenance. Clean with a damp cloth, under no circumstances use fibers or abrasive agents.
